
itools 0.75.0 (2009/1X/XX)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.log              itools.srx
  itools.core             itools.mail             itools.stl
  itools.csv              itools.odf              itools.tmx
  itools.datatypes        itools.office           itools.uri
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.vfs
  itools.git              itools.pkg              itools.web
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.workflow
  itools.html             itools.relaxng          itools.xapian
  itools.http             itools.rest             itools.xliff
  itools.i18n             itools.rss              itools.xml
  itools.ical             itools.soup             itools.xmlfile


git log --stat --no-merges 326787a7eedb9~1..master

Now itools uses the HTTP server from the libsoup [1] library.  This
brings a better support of the HTTP protocol and improved performance.
As a side effect the itools.soup package has been added, it is a
minimalistic Python wrapper around the libsoup library.

The web stack (itools.http, itools.web) has considerably changed,
partly because of the introduction of libsoup.  Overall the programming
interface is friendlier, and the performance much better.  For further
details check the upgrade notes and the documentation.

The new package itools.log is a simple alternative to the Pythons's
standard library "logging" package.  It is inspired by the logging
facilities from the Glib [2] library, and may eventually become just
a wrapper.

The new itools.mail package allows to send emails asynchronously, it
uses the Glibs loop.  This feature has been moved from ikaaro [3].

Refactor common code in itools.csv and itools.ical, general cleanup,
including moving some features to ikaaro.

